  "vesicular_monoamine_transporter": {
    "title": "Vesicular Monoamine Transporter (VMAT)",
    "primaryType": "structure",
    "tags": [
      "Pharmacology",
      "Neurology",
      "Neuroscience",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology",
      "Neuropharmacology",
      "Transporters"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>The <b>Vesicular Monoamine Transporter (VMAT)</b> is an integral membrane protein responsible for packaging monoamines (such as [[dopamine]], [[norepinephrine]], and [[serotonin]]) from the cytosol into synaptic vesicles, thereby enabling their subsequent release into the synaptic cleft and protecting them from degradation by [[monoamine_oxidase]].</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Function:</b> Transports monoamines into presynaptic vesicles against a concentration gradient using a proton gradient.</li><li><b>Pharmacology:</b> Inhibited by drugs like [[tetrabenazine]], [[deutetrabenazine]], and [[reserpine]].</li><li><b>Clinical Use:</b> Inhibition of VMAT2 depletes dopamine stores, which is therapeutic for hyperkinetic movement disorders like [[huntington_disease]] (chorea) and [[tardive_dyskinesia]].</li><li><b>Adverse Effects of Inhibition:</b> Depression, sedation, and parkinsonism due to monoamine depletion.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Remember that <b>Reserpine</b> irreversibly blocks VMAT, while <b>Tetrabenazine</b> is a reversible inhibitor used for Huntington's chorea.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>VMAT</b> is the gatekeeper for neurotransmitter storage; its inhibition leads to the depletion of presynaptic monoamines (dopamine, norepinephrine), making it a target for treating hyperkinetic disorders at the risk of causing depression or parkinsonism.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Cytosolic Dopamine] -->|VMAT2| B[Synaptic Vesicle]; B -->|Release| C[Synaptic Cleft]; D[Tetrabenazine] --x|Inhibits| A;"
    },
    "connections": [
      {
        "type": "is_inhibited_by",
        "to": "tetrabenazine"
      },
      {
        "type": "is_inhibited_by",
        "to": "reserpine"
      },
      {
        "type": "transports",
        "to": "dopamine"
      },
      {
