      "definition": "<p>The <b>Medial Geniculate Nucleus (MGN)</b> is a specific sensory relay nucleus within the [[thalamus]] that receives auditory information from the [[inferior_colliculus]] and projects it via the auditory radiations to the [[primary_auditory_cortex]] in the temporal lobe.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Input:</b> [[inferior_colliculus]] (via the brachium of the inferior colliculus).</li><li><b>Output:</b> Auditory radiations to the [[primary_auditory_cortex]] (Transverse temporal gyri of Heschl).</li><li><b>Function:</b> Relaying auditory information (Hearing).</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Mnemonic: <b>M</b> is for <b>M</b>usic (Hearing) = <b>M</b>GN.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>Medial Geniculate Nucleus</b> serves as the mandatory thalamic relay station for all ascending auditory information en route to the cortex.</p>",
