    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>The <b>Ventral Posterolateral Nucleus (VPL)</b> is the major somatosensory relay nucleus of the [[thalamus]] responsible for transmitting sensation from the <u>body</u> (vibration, pain, pressure, proprioception, temperature) to the primary somatosensory cortex.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Input:</b> [[spinothalamic_tract]] (pain/temp) and [[dorsal_column_medial_lemniscus]] (touch/proprioception).</li><li><b>Output:</b> Primary [[somatosensory_cortex]] (Postcentral gyrus).</li><li><b>Information Type:</b> Somatosensory input from the <b>Body</b> (neck down).</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Differentiate from VPM (Face). Remember: V<b>P</b>L is for the <b>P</b>eriphery (Body).</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>Ventral Posterolateral Nucleus</b> integrates all somatosensory modalities from the <b>body</b> and relays them to the cortex; lesions here result in contralateral hemianesthesia of the body.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Spinothalamic Tract] --> B[VPL]; C[Medial Lemniscus] --> B; B --> D[Somatosensory Cortex];"
    },
