      "Nutritional Deficiencies"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Subacute Combined Degeneration (SCD)</b> is a progressive degeneration of the spinal cord caused by [[vitamin_b12_deficiency]], characterized by the demyelination of the <u>dorsal columns</u>, <u>lateral corticospinal tracts</u>, and <u>spinocerebellar tracts</u>.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Pathophysiology:</b> Vitamin B12 deficiency leads to accumulation of methylmalonic acid, which impairs myelin synthesis, causing vacuolar degeneration of spinal tracts.</li><li><b>Affected Tracts:</b><br> 1. <b>Dorsal Columns:</b> Loss of proprioception/vibration (sensory ataxia, +Romberg).<br> 2. <b>Lateral Corticospinal:</b> Spastic paresis, hyperreflexia, +Babinski (Upper Motor Neuron signs).<br> 3. <b>Spinocerebellar:</b> Ataxia.</li><li><b>Clinical Presentation:</b> Paresthesias, gait ataxia, weakness, and eventual spastic paralysis.</li><li><b>Associations:</b> Pernicious anemia, gastric bypass, vegan diet, diphyllobothrium latum infection.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> \"Combined\" refers to the combination of Sensory (Dorsal column) and Motor (Corticospinal) deficits. Always check B12 in patients with neuropathy/ataxia.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Subacute Combined Degeneration</b> is the classic neurological manifestation of B12 deficiency, presenting as a unique mix of <b>UMN signs</b> (spasticity) and <b>loss of proprioception/vibration</b> due to specific white matter tract demyelination.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Vitamin B12 Deficiency] --> B[Elevated Methylmalonic Acid]; B --> C[Abnormal Myelin Synthesis]; C --> D[Demyelination]; D --> E[Dorsal Column Loss]; D --> F[Corticospinal Tract Loss];"
