  "adenohypophysis": {
    "title": "Adenohypophysis (Anterior Pituitary)",
    "primaryType": "structure",
    "tags": [
      "Endocrinology",
      "Anatomy",
      "Embryology",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Endocrinology",
      "Pituitary Gland",
      "Anterior Lobe"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>The <b>Adenohypophysis</b> is the glandular anterior lobe of the [[pituitary_gland]], derived from oral ectoderm ([[rathke_pouch]]), which synthesizes and secretes six major hormones in response to hypothalamic releasing factors delivered via the hypophyseal portal system.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Embryology:</b> Derived from <b>Rathke's Pouch</b> (surface ectoderm), unlike the neurohypophysis (neuroectoderm).</li><li><b>Hormones (FLAT PiG):</b> <b>F</b>SH, <b>L</b>H, <b>A</b>CTH, <b>T</b>SH (Basophils); <b>P</b>rolactin, <b>G</b>H (Acidophils).</li><li><b>Regulation:</b> Controlled by the [[hypothalamus]] via the hypophyseal portal system (blood), not direct neural connection.</li><li><b>Pathology:</b> [[pituitary_adenoma]] (e.g., Prolactinoma), [[sheehan_syndrome]] (ischemic necrosis post-partum), [[craniopharyngioma]] (Rathke's pouch remnant).</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Acidophils (GH, Prolactin) stain pink; Basophils (FSH, LH, ACTH, TSH) stain blue. \"B-FLAT\".</li></ul>",
