      "definition": "<p><b>Angle-Closure Glaucoma</b> is an ophthalmic emergency caused by the physical obstruction of the anterior chamber angle (specifically the trabecular meshwork) by the iris, preventing aqueous humor drainage and leading to a rapid spike in [[intraocular_pressure]].</p>",
