      "takeAway": "<p><b>Angle-Closure Glaucoma</b> is a painful emergency of raised intraocular pressure due to mechanical blockage of outflow, triggered by pupil dilation and requiring immediate pressure reduction and pupillary constriction.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Pupil Dilation] --> B[Iris blocks Trabecular Meshwork]; B --> C[Aqueous Humor Trapped]; C --> D[Rapid Increase in IOP]; D --> E[Optic Nerve Damage/Pain];"
