      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Location:</b> Ventral (anterior) portion of the neural tube.</li><li><b>Signaling Factor:</b> Induced by <b>Sonic Hedgehog (SHH)</b> from the [[notochord]]/floor plate.</li><li><b>Derivatives:</b> Motor nuclei of the [[spinal_cord]] (ventral horn) and brainstem motor nuclei (e.g., Hypoglossal nucleus).</li><li><b>Orientation:</b> Ventral = Motor (Basal); Dorsal = Sensory (Alar).</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Remember <b>B</b>asal = <b>B</b>elly (Ventral) = Motor.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>Basal Plate</b> is the ventral, motor division of the developing nervous system, regulated by SHH signaling, standing in contrast to the dorsal, sensory [[alar_plate]].</p>",
