    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>The <b>Limbic System</b> is a complex set of brain structures (including the [[hippocampus]], [[amygdala]], [[hypothalamus]], and cingulate gyrus) responsible for regulating <u>emotion, behavior, motivation, long-term memory</u>, and olfaction.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Key Structures:</b><br> - <b>Hippocampus:</b> Memory formation.<br> - <b>Amygdala:</b> Emotion (Fear/Aggression).<br> - <b>Mammillary Bodies:</b> Memory (damaged in Wernicke-Korsakoff).<br> - <b>Nucleus Accumbens:</b> Reward/Addiction.<br> - <b>Cingulate Gyrus:</b> Emotion/Pain processing.</li><li><b>Function (The 5 F's):</b> <b>F</b>eeding, <b>F</b>leeing, <b>F</b>ighting, <b>F</b>eeling, and <b>S</b>ex.</li><li><b>Circuitry:</b> Papez Circuit (Hippocampus &rarr; Fornix &rarr; Mammillary Bodies &rarr; Thalamus &rarr; Cingulate &rarr; Hippocampus).</li><li><b>Pathology:</b> [[kluver_bucy_syndrome]] (HSV-1 damage to amygdala), Wernicke-Korsakoff (Mammillary bodies).</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>Limbic System</b> integrates primitive drives (Feeding, Fighting, Sex) with higher cognitive functions (Memory, Emotion); its dysfunction leads to profound behavioral and amnestic syndromes.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Hippocampus] -->|Fornix| B[Mammillary Bodies]; B -->|Mammillothalamic Tract| C[Anterior Thalamic Nucleus]; C --> D[Cingulate Gyrus]; D --> A;"
