      "definition": "<p><b>Benzodiazepines</b> (e.g., Diazepam, Lorazepam, Midazolam) are CNS depressants that act as positive allosteric modulators of the <u>GABA<sub>A</sub> receptor</u>, increasing the <b>frequency</b> of chloride channel opening.</p>",
