    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Bone Morphogenetic Proteins (BMPs)</b> are signaling molecules (TGF-&beta; superfamily) secreted by the overlying ectoderm/roof plate during neural tube development, which induce the differentiation of the <u>dorsal</u> aspect of the neural tube ([[alar_plate]]). </p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Function in Neuroembryology:</b> BMP signaling induces the <b>Alar Plate</b> (Sensory).</li><li><b>Opposing Signal:</b> <b>Sonic Hedgehog (SHH)</b> from the notochord induces the Basal Plate (Motor).</li><li><b>General Function:</b> Bone and cartilage formation, dorsal-ventral patterning.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> <b>B</b>MP = <b>B</b>ack (Dorsal/Sensory). SHH = Stomach side (Ventral/Motor).</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>BMPs</b> provide the dorsalizing signal for the neural tube, establishing the sensory [[alar_plate]], in opposition to the ventralizing SHH signal.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Ectoderm] -->|Secretes BMP| B[Dorsal Neural Tube]; B --> C[Alar Plate Differentiation]; C --> D[Sensory Neurons];"
