      "definition": "<p><b>Botulinum Toxin</b> is a neurotoxin produced by <i>Clostridium botulinum</i> that acts as a protease, cleaving <u>SNARE proteins</u> (e.g., SNAP-25, synaptobrevin) to prevent the presynaptic release of [[acetylcholine]], causing flaccid paralysis.</p>",
