      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Functional Anatomy:</b> The Vermis controls medial motor systems (trunk, proximal muscles, head/neck).</li><li><b>Clinical Findings:</b><br> - <b>Truncal Ataxia:</b> Inability to sit or stand without swaying.<br> - <b>Gait Ataxia:</b> Wide-based, unsteady gait (\"Drunken Sailor\").<br> - <b>Nystagmus/Head Titubation.</b></li><li><b>Etiologies:</b> Chronic [[alcohol_use_disorder]] (selectively damages anterior vermis), Medulloblastoma (children).</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Medial lesion = Medial body (Trunk). Lateral lesion = Lateral body (Limbs).</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>Lesions of the <b>Cerebellar Vermis</b> cause central/truncal instability (truncal ataxia), classically seen in alcoholic cerebellar degeneration.</p>",
