      "definition": "<p><b>Cerebral Perfusion</b> is the delivery of blood to the brain tissue, strictly regulated by <u>autoregulation</u> to maintain constant flow across a range of pressures, primarily driven by arterial <b>PCO<sub>2</sub></b>.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Regulation:</b><br> - <b>PCO<sub>2</sub>:</b> Potent vasodilator. &uarr; PCO<sub>2</sub> &rarr; &uarr; CBF. (Linear relationship).<br> - <b>PO<sub>2</sub>:</b> Minimal effect until severe hypoxia (<50 mmHg) &rarr; vasodilation.<br> - <b>Autoregulation:</b> Constant CBF between MAP 60-140 mmHg.</li><li><b>Therapeutic Hyperventilation:</b> Decreases PCO<sub>2</sub> &rarr; Vasoconstriction &rarr; Decreases Cerebral Blood Volume &rarr; Lowers [[intracranial_pressure]] (acute management).</li><li><b>Cushing Reflex:</b> Response to ischemia from high ICP: Hypertension, Bradycardia, Respiratory Irregularity.</li></ul>",
