      "definition": "<p><b>Circadian Rhythm</b> is the endogenous 24-hour physiological cycle regulating sleep-wake patterns, hormone secretion (e.g., Cortisol, Melatonin), and body temperature, primarily controlled by the <u>Suprachiasmatic Nucleus (SCN)</u> of the hypothalamus.</p>",
