    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>The <b>Dentate Nucleus</b> is the largest and most lateral of the <u>deep cerebellar nuclei</u>, responsible for planning, initiating, and controlling voluntary movements via the dentato-rubro-thalamic tract.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Input:</b> Receives input from the <b>Lateral Hemispheres</b> of the cerebellum (Cerebrocerebellum).</li><li><b>Output:</b> Projects to the Contralateral <b>Thalamus</b> (VL/VA nuclei) and Red Nucleus via the [[superior_cerebellar_peduncle]].</li><li><b>Function:</b> Planning and coordination of fine motor movements.</li><li><b>Mnemonics:</b> Deep nuclei from Lateral to Medial: \"<b>D</b>on't <b>E</b>at <b>G</b>reasy <b>F</b>oods\" (<b>D</b>entate, <b>E</b>mboliform, <b>G</b>lobose, <b>F</b>astigial).</li><li><b>Lesions:</b> Cause [[dysmetria]], intention tremor, and \"decomposition of movement\" in the extremities.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>Dentate Nucleus</b> is the output center for the cerebrocerebellum, crucial for motor planning; lesions result in ipsilateral limb ataxia and intention tremor.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Cerebellar Hemispheres] --> B[Dentate Nucleus]; B -->|Superior Cerebellar Peduncle| C[Contralateral Thalamus VL]; C --> D[Motor Cortex]; D --> E[Corticospinal Tract];"
