    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Desflurane</b> is a halogenated <i>inhaled anesthetic</i> characterized by a very low blood-gas partition coefficient, resulting in rapid induction and recovery.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Properties:</b> Low blood solubility (Rapid onset/offset). Pungent odor (can cause airway irritation/coughing).</li><li><b>Mechanism:</b> Potentiates GABA<sub>A</sub> receptors; inhibits NMDA receptors.</li><li><b>Pharmacokinetics:</b> Low blood/gas coefficient = Fast induction.</li><li><b>Adverse Effects:</b> <b>Airway irritation</b> (laryngospasm), [[malignant_hyperthermia]], respiratory depression, increased cerebral blood flow (increased ICP).</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Fast on/fast off, but smells bad (irritates airway). Don't use for induction in asthmatics.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Desflurane</b> allows for rapid anesthetic control due to low solubility but is limited by airway irritation; like all halogenated gases, it can trigger malignant hyperthermia.</p>",
      "mermaid": ""
