      "definition": "<p><b>Diabetes Mellitus</b> causes significant neurological morbidity via microvascular ischemia and metabolic toxicity (sorbitol accumulation), leading to peripheral neuropathy, cranial nerve palsies, and autonomic dysfunction.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Diabetic Neuropathy:</b> \"Stocking-glove\" sensory loss (distal symmetric polyneuropathy). Small fiber injury = Pain/Temp loss. Large fiber injury = Vibration/Proprioception loss.</li><li><b>Cranial Mononeuropathy:</b> <b>CN III Palsy:</b> Ischemic damage to central motor fibers. <u>Pupil is spared</u> (peripheral parasympathetic fibers fed by pial vessels are preserved). Down-and-out eye.</li><li><b>Autonomic Neuropathy:</b> Gastroparesis, orthostatic hypotension, erectile dysfunction, silent MI.</li><li><b>Pathophysiology:</b> Osmotic damage (Sorbitol accumulation via Aldose Reductase) and microangiopathy (vasa nervorum ischemia).</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Diabetes</b> damages nerves via sorbitol and ischemia; classic neuro findings include stocking-glove neuropathy and a <b>pupil-sparing</b> CN III palsy.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Hyperglycemia] --> B[Sorbitol Accumulation]; A --> C[Microvascular Ischemia]; B --> D[Osmotic Damage to Schwann Cells]; C --> E[Vasa Nervorum Occlusion]; D & E --> F[Demyelination/Axonal Loss];"
