      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Afferent Limb:</b> Retina &rarr; [[optic_nerve]] (CN II) &rarr; Pretectal Nucleus (Midbrain).</li><li><b>Integration:</b> Pretectal Nucleus projects bilaterally to the [[edinger_westphal_nucleus]].</li><li><b>Efferent Limb:</b> Edinger-Westphal &rarr; [[oculomotor_nerve]] (CN III) parasympathetics &rarr; Ciliary Ganglion &rarr; Sphincter Pupillae.</li><li><b>Clinical Significance:</b> Loss of direct reflex with preserved consensual response (in the other eye) indicates an <b>efferent</b> (CN III) defect in the illuminated eye. Loss of both suggests an <b>afferent</b> (CN II) defect.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>Direct Light Reflex</b> tests the ipsilateral sensory (CN II) and motor (CN III) arc; intactness confirms the pathway from retina to midbrain and back to the iris.</p>",
