  "dura_mater": {
    "title": "Dura Mater",
    "primaryType": "structure",
    "tags": [
      "Neurology",
      "Anatomy",
      "Meninges",
      "USMLE"
    ],
    "classificationPath": [
      "Neurology",
      "Brain Anatomy",
      "Meninges"
    ],
    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>The <b>Dura Mater</b> is the tough, outermost layer of the [[meninges]], composed of dense fibrous connective tissue, which forms the dural venous sinuses and partitions the cranial cavity (e.g., [[falx_cerebri]], [[tentorium_cerebelli]]).</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Layers:</b> Periosteal (attached to skull) and Meningeal (inner). Separation creates <b>Venous Sinuses</b>.</li><li><b>Innervation:</b> Branches of [[trigeminal_nerve]] (CN V) &rarr; source of headache pain (brain tissue itself has no pain receptors).</li><li><b>Spaces:</b><br> - <i>Epidural Space:</i> Potential space above dura (site of [[epidural_hematoma]] - MMA rupture).<br> - <i>Subdural Space:</i> Potential space below dura (site of [[subdural_hematoma]] - Bridging vein rupture).</li><li><b>Folds:</b> Falx Cerebri, Tentorium Cerebelli (sites of herniation).</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>Dura Mater</b> provides structural support, houses venous sinuses, and defines the epidural and subdural spaces, critical sites for intracranial hemorrhage.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Skull] --> B[Epidural Space]; B --> C[Dura Mater]; C --> D[Subdural Space]; D --> E[Arachnoid Mater]; E --> F[Subarachnoid Space];"
    },
    "connections": [
      {
        "type": "forms_boundary_of",
        "to": "epidural_hematoma"
      },
      {
        "type": "forms_boundary_of",
        "to": "subdural_hematoma"
      },
      {
        "type": "contains",
        "to": "dural_venous_sinuses"
      },
      {
        "type": "innervated_by",
        "to": "trigeminal_nerve"
