      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Pathophysiology:</b> Impaired resorption of endolymph (via endolymphatic sac) &rarr; Increased pressure &rarr; Distortion/Rupture of membranous labyrinth.</li><li><b>Clinical Presentation (Meniere's):</b> Episodic <b>Vertigo</b>, fluctuating <b>Hearing Loss</b> (sensorineural), <b>Tinnitus</b>, and aural fullness.</li><li><b>Treatment:</b> Low salt diet, Diuretics (e.g., [[acetazolamide]], HCTZ) to reduce fluid pressure.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> \"Hydrops\" = Water/Fluid. Meniere's is \"glaucoma of the ear.\"</li></ul>",
