    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Broca Aphasia</b> (Expressive Aphasia) is a non-fluent aphasia caused by a lesion in the posterior inferior frontal gyrus ([[broca_area]]), characterized by sparse, halting speech, impaired repetition, but relatively preserved comprehension.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Lesion:</b> Left Inferior Frontal Gyrus.</li><li><b>Vessel:</b> Superior division of the [[middle_cerebral_artery]].</li><li><b>Clinical:</b> \"Broken\" speech (agrammatic), frustration (insight intact). Often associated with right hemiparesis (face/arm).</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Broca Aphasia</b> destroys speech production (\"Expressive\") while sparing comprehension, localizing to the frontal lobe.</p>",
