    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Eyelid Disorders</b> encompass inflammatory, infectious, and structural pathologies of the eyelid, including blepharitis, hordeolum, chalazion, and cellulitis.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>[[blepharitis]]:</b> Chronic inflammation of lid margins (crusting).</li><li><b>[[hordeolum]] (Stye):</b> Acute, <b>painful</b> infection of eyelash follicle or Zeis gland (usually S. aureus).</li><li><b>[[chalazion]]:</b> Chronic, <b>painless</b> lipogranuloma of Meibomian gland.</li><li><b>Preseptal Cellulitis:</b> Infection anterior to orbital septum (mild).</li><li><b>Orbital Cellulitis:</b> Infection posterior to septum (pain with movement, proptosis, vision loss). Emergency.</li><li><b>Ptosis:</b> Drooping (CN III palsy, Horner's, MG).</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>Differentiating eyelid lumps relies on pain: Hordeolum hurts, Chalazion is chill (painless). Orbital cellulitis is a vision-threatening emergency.</p>",
      "mermaid": ""
    },
