      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Pathophysiology:</b> Autoimmune attack on <b>Schwann cells</b>/myelin (or axons) via molecular mimicry following infection (e.g., <i>[[campylobacter_jejuni]]</i>, CMV, Zika).</li><li><b>Clinical Presentation:</b> Symmetric <b>Ascending Paralysis</b> (Legs &rarr; Arms &rarr; Face/Respiratory). Absent DTRs. Autonomic dysregulation (arrhythmias, BP lability).</li><li><b>Diagnosis:</b> CSF shows <b>[[albuminocytologic_dissociation]]</b> (High protein, normal cells). Nerve conduction studies show slowing.</li><li><b>Treatment:</b> <b>IVIG</b> or <b>Plasmapheresis</b>. Supportive care (ventilator). Steroids are ineffective.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> The most common cause of acute flaccid paralysis. Monitor <b>Vital Capacity</b> for respiratory failure.</li></ul>",
