    "content": {
      "definition": "<p><b>Horner Syndrome</b> is a clinical triad of <b>ptosis</b>, <b>miosis</b>, and <b>anhidrosis</b> caused by the interruption of the <u>oculosympathetic pathway</u> anywhere along its three-neuron chain.</p>",
