      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Genetics:</b> <b>CAG</b> repeats on Chromosome 4. <b>Autosomal Dominant</b>. Demonstrates <b>Anticipation</b> (worsens in subsequent generations).</li><li><b>Pathophysiology:</b> Mutant huntingtin protein causes excitotoxicity (NMDA) and loss of <b>GABAergic</b> neurons in the [[striatum]] ([[caudate_nucleus]] > putamen).</li><li><b>Neurotransmitters:</b> Decreased <b>GABA</b>, Decreased <b>ACh</b>, Increased <b>Dopamine</b>.</li><li><b>Clinical Features:</b><br> - <i>Motor:</i> [[chorea]] (dance-like movements), Athetosis.<br> - <i>Psychiatric:</i> Depression, Aggression, Psychosis.<br> - <i>Cognitive:</i> Dementia.</li><li><b>Imaging:</b> Caudate atrophy causes enlargement of frontal horns of lateral ventricles (<b>\"Boxcar Ventricles\"</b>).</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> \"<b>C</b>audate loss, <b>A</b>Ch/GABA loss, <b>G</b>enetic repeats (CAG) on Chr <b>4</b>.\"</li></ul>",
