    "content": {
      "definition": "<p>The <b>Indirect Pathway</b> of the basal ganglia suppresses unwanted movement by increasing the inhibitory output of the GPi/SNr to the thalamus, modulated by [[dopamine]] binding to D2 receptors.</p>",
      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Circuitry:</b> Cortex &rarr; Striatum (GABA) &rarr; Inhibits <b>GPe</b> &rarr; Disinhibits <b>[[subthalamic_nucleus]]</b> &rarr; Excites <b>GPi/SNr</b> &rarr; Inhibits Thalamus &rarr; <b>Decreased Motion</b>.</li><li><b>Dopamine Effect:</b> Nigrostriatal dopamine binds <b>D2 Receptors</b> (Gi - inhibitory) in the striatum &rarr; <u>Inhibits</u> the Indirect Pathway &rarr; Allows movement.</li><li><b>Pathology:</b> <br> - <i>Loss of D2 stimulation (Parkinson's):</i> Indirect pathway runs wild &rarr; rigidity/bradykinesia.<br> - <i>Loss of Indirect Pathway (Huntington's):</i> Early loss of striatal GABA/Enk neurons &rarr; Hyperkinesia (Chorea).</li><li><b>Mnemonic:</b> <b>In</b>direct = <b>In</b>hibits movement. D<b>2</b> = Inhibition.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p>The <b>Indirect Pathway</b> acts as a brake on movement; dopamine lifts this brake via D2 receptors. Loss of this pathway leads to chorea (Huntington's), while overactivity leads to parkinsonism.</p>",
      "mermaid": "graph TD; A[Cortex] --(+)--> B[Striatum]; B --(-)|GABA| C[GPe]; C --(-)|GABA| D[Subthalamic Nucleus]; D --(+)|Glutamate| E[GPi/SNr]; E --(-)|GABA| F[Thalamus]; F --(+)|Glutamate| G[Motor Cortex]; H[SNc Dopamine] --(-)|D2| B;"
