      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Origin:</b> <b>Germinal Matrix</b> (highly vascularized area in subventricular zone, involutes by term). Fragile vessels rupture due to hypoxia/BP fluctuations.</li><li><b>Risk Factors:</b> <b>Prematurity</b> (<32 weeks), Low Birth Weight (<1500g), RDS.</li><li><b>Clinical Presentation:</b> Hypotonia, seizures, bulging fontanelle, anemia, apnea. Can be asymptomatic.</li><li><b>Complications:</b> Post-hemorrhagic <b>[[hydrocephalus]]</b> (clot obstructs CSF flow), Cerebral Palsy.</li><li><b>Screening:</b> Cranial Ultrasound.</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> Look for a preemie with sudden drop in hematocrit and altered mental status.</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>Intraventricular Hemorrhage</b> is a complication of prematurity caused by the rupture of the fragile germinal matrix capillaries, potentially leading to hydrocephalus and neurodevelopmental delay.</p>",
