      "atAGlance": "<ul><li><b>Pathogenesis:</b> Reactivation &rarr; Infection/Lysis of <b>[[oligodendrocytes]]</b> &rarr; Demyelination.</li><li><b>Disease:</b> <b>Progressive Multifocal Leukoencephalopathy (PML)</b>.</li><li><b>Clinical:</b> Rapidly progressive focal neurologic deficits (weakness, visual field defects, ataxia, dementia). Usually fatal.</li><li><b>Imaging:</b> MRI shows multifocal, non-enhancing white matter lesions (no mass effect).</li><li><b>USMLE Tip:</b> \"JC\" = <b>J</b>unky <b>C</b>erebrum (Demyelination). Don't confuse with BK virus (<b>B</b>ad <b>K</b>idney - transplant nephropathy).</li></ul>",
      "takeAway": "<p><b>JC Virus</b> targets oligodendrocytes in immunosuppressed patients, causing the fatal demyelinating disease PML.</p>",
